# Cursor AI Rules for LLM-Based Code Smell Detection Research Project

## Project Overview
This is a research project evaluating LLMs for code smell detection using the MaRV dataset:
- **Core Stack:** Python + Ollama (local LLM) + ChromaDB + LangGraph + RAG
- **Purpose:** Empirical evaluation comparing LLM vs traditional static analysis tools
- **Dataset:** MaRV (Manually Validated Refactoring)
- **Status:** Planning & Documentation Phase Complete, Implementation starting
- **Submission Deadline:** May 26, 2026

## Code Style and Standards

### Python (All Modules)
- Use Python 3.11+
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Maximum line length: 120 characters
- Use type hints for all function signatures
- Use docstrings (Google style) for all public functions and classes
- Prefer async/await for I/O operations when dealing with LLM calls
- Use Pydantic for data validation
- Prioritize reproducibility and experiment tracking

### File Organization
```
code-smell/
├── src/                   # Core Python modules
│   ├── llm_client.py     # Ollama client wrapper
│   ├── rag_pipeline.py   # RAG implementation
│   ├── analysis_coordinator.py
│   └── ...
├── data/                  # Datasets and ground truth
│   ├── datasets/
│   │   ├── marv/         # MaRV dataset
│   │   ├── qualitas_corpus/
│   │   └── smelly_code/
│   └── ground_truth/
├── exp/                   # Experiment results
│   ├── baseline/
│   ├── rag_experiments/
│   └── ablation_studies/
├── results/               # Benchmark results for paper
│   ├── predictions/
│   ├── confusion_matrices/
│   ├── performance/
│   └── metrics/
├── scripts/               # Utility scripts
├── visualization/         # Web-based visualization
└── paper/                 # LaTeX source files
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Files**: snake_case (e.g., `code_review_service.py`)
- **Classes**: PascalCase (e.g., `CodeReviewService`)
- **Functions/Variables**: snake_case (e.g., `analyze_code_smell`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `MAX_CHUNK_SIZE`)
- **Private methods**: prefix with underscore (e.g., `_process_internal`)

### Import Organization
```python
# Standard library imports
import os
