## File Naming Conventions

### Experiment Results
- `{experiment_type}_{model}_{config}_{timestamp}.json`
- Example: `rag_experiment_llama3_k5_20260226_143022.json`

### Predictions
- `{tool_name}_{dataset}_{timestamp}.csv`
- Example: `llm_rag_marv_validation_20260226.csv`

### Metrics
- `{metric_name}_{experiment_id}.csv`
- Example: `confusion_matrix_exp001.csv`

### Logs
- `{script_name}_{timestamp}.log`
- Example: `run_baseline_20260226_143022.log`

## Quick Reference

### Key Files
- `config.py` - All configuration parameters
- `requirements.txt` - Python dependencies with pinned versions
- `PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md` - Directory structure documentation
- `docs/planning/WBS.md` - Work breakdown structure and progress

### Key Directories
- `src/` - Core Python modules (llm_client, rag_pipeline, etc.)
- `scripts/` - Experiment and utility scripts
- `data/datasets/marv/` - MaRV dataset (read-only)
- `results/` - All experimental outputs
- `chromadb_store/` - Vector database (gitignored)
- `cache/` - LLM response cache (gitignored)

### Common Commands
```bash
# Activate environment
source venv/bin/activate

# Run experiment
python scripts/run_experiment.py --experiment-name baseline_llm

